18/11/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Presenting the European Commission's recent report on Serbia-Montenegro to a committee of the Serbian Parliament, EU delegation head Josep Lloveras welcomed the progress achieved so far, while stressing there is still much to be done. He urged the authorities Thursday (17 November) to finalise co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague and to strive for a constructive dialogue with Pristina in light of the upcoming negotiations on Kosovo's future status. As for the challenges Serbia-Montenegro faces on its road to eventual EU membership, Lloveras reiterated that the EC stands ready to help.
Also Thursday, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic was in Strasbourg, France, attending the session of the Council of Europe's Committee of Ministers. He called for more protection of the rights of the Serb minority in Kosovo. (Tanjug, RTS, B92, CoE Web Site - 17/11/05)
